						functions, and duties of a psychiatric technician, in which event the record of the conviction shall be conclusive evidence of the conviction. The board may inquire into the circumstances surrounding the commission of the crime in order to fix the degree of discipline.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(f) Impersonating any applicant or acting as proxy for an applicant in any examination required by this chapter.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(g) Impersonating another practitioner, or permitting another person to use the licensee’s certificate or license.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(h) The use of excessive force upon or the mistreatment or abuse of any patient.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(i) Aiding or assisting, or agreeing to aid or assist any person or persons, whether a
